# APM dependency cache (resolved from apm.lock.yaml on `apm install`).
# The lockfile IS committed; the materialized modules are not.
apm_modules/

# Harness-deploy output (apm install, target: copilot). This repo self-consumes:
# .apm/ is the source of truth and `apm install` materializes primitives below.
#
# .github/agents/ is COMMITTED on purpose (it is NOT ignored): it is the
# reviewable snapshot of the external awesome-copilot agents pulled via
# dependencies. Bumping a dep (`apm update`) + re-running `apm install` shows the
# real agent-text diff in the PR — a guard against prompt-hijacking. Everything
# else below is trivially regenerable from .apm/ and stays out of git.
.agents/
.github/instructions/
.github/hooks/

# Deployed prompt copies (regenerated by `apm install` from .apm/prompts/).
# Ignore the generated copies; keep the two authored repo-local prompts.
# When adding a new authored .github/prompts/ file, negate it here too.
.github/prompts/*.prompt.md
!.github/prompts/copilot-add-prompt.prompt.md
!.github/prompts/copilot-generate-informal-message.prompt.md